headline: Netflix to double sales, American Air free wi-fi, HPE & Elliot
summary: Brad Smith takes a closer look at the trending stories on Wall Street as part of today's Market Minute. Netflix (NFLX) stock gains on reports the company is aiming for a $1 trillion market capitalization and to double revenue by 2030. American Airlines (AAL) is partnering with AT&T (T) to offer AAdvantage members free in-flight wi-fi. HPE (HPE) is in focus as activist investor Elliot Management builds a $1.5 billion stake in the company. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
